# Server Environment Variables

Copy this file to `.env` in the `server/` directory and fill in your values.

```env
# Database Connection String from Neon
# Format: postgresql://user:password@host/database
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://your_user:your_password@your_host.neon.tech/your_db

# JWT Secret for signing tokens (use a random string of 32+ characters)
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-key-change-this-to-something-very-random-and-long

# Server Port
PORT=4000

# Frontend URL (for CORS and email links)
CLIENT_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Email Configuration (Gmail)
SMTP_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
SMTP_PORT=465
SMTP_USER=your-email@gmail.com
SMTP_PASS=your-app-specific-password

# Node Environment
NODE_ENV=development
```

## How to Generate Values

### JWT_SECRET
```bash
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

### Gmail App Password
1. Enable 2FA on your Google Account
2. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
3. Select "Mail" and "Windows Computer" (or your device)
4. Generate a 16-character password
5. Copy and paste it here

### DATABASE_URL
1. Create a free Neon account at https://neon.tech
2. Create a new project
3. Copy the connection string from the dashboard
